A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this POKéMON. Bulbasaur can be seen napping in bright sunlight. There is a seed on its back. The flame on its tail shows the strength of its life force. If it is weak, the flame also burns weakly. If it's healthy, the flame on the tip of its tail will burn vigor­ ously, even if it gets a bit wet. The fire on the tip of its tail is a measure of its life. If healthy, its tail burns intensely. Obviously prefers hot places. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail. The flame at the tip of its tail makes a sound as it burns. You can only hear it in quiet places. The flame that burns at the tip of its tail is an indication of its emotions. The flame wavers when CHARMANDER is enjoying itself. If the POKéMON becomes enraged, the flame burns fiercely. Bulbasaur is a small, quadruped Pokémon that has blue-green body with darker blue-green spots. It has red eyes with white pupils and pointed, ear-like structures on top of its head.
Ivysaur is a dinosaur-like Pokémon. It has blue-green skin with darker patches. On its back it has an enlarged plant bulb, which grows as the Pokémon does.
Venusaur is a large dinosaur-like Pokémon. A large palm tree-like plant grows out of its back. The plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy.
A small, lizard-like Pokémon with large eyes and two small legs. It can use its vines to attack enemies.
A small, reptilian Pokémon with flames on its tail. It is known for its fiery personality.
A massive, plant-like Pokémon with large leaves and powerful arms. It is said to have the power to heal itself and others.

Without pity, its sharp claws destroy foes. If it encounters a strong enemy, it becomes agitated, and the flame on its tail flares with a bluish white color. If it becomes agitated during battle, it spouts intense flames, incinerating its surroundings. Tough fights could excite this POKéMON. When excited, it may blow out bluish- white flames. It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws. In the rocky mountains where Charmeleon live, their fiery tails shine at night like stars. It is very hot­ headed by nature, so it constantly seeks opponents. It calms down only when it wins. CHARMELEON mercilessly destroys its foes using its sharp claws. When it feels threatened, it draws its legs inside its shell and sprays water from its mouth. Its shell is not just for protection. Its rounded shape and the grooves on its surface minimize resistance in water, enabling SQUIRTLE to swim at high speeds. When it retracts its long neck into its shell, it squirts out water with vigorous force. It shelters itself in its shell then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity. Blastoise has water spouts that protrude from its shell. The water spouts are very accurate. They can shoot bullets of water with enough accuracy to strike empty cans from a distance of over 160 feet. It deliberately makes itself heavy so it can with­ stand the recoil of the water jets it fires. BLASTOISE has water spouts that protrude from its shell. The water spouts are very accurate. They can shoot bullets of water with enough accuracy to strike empty cans from a distance of over 160 feet. The pressurized water jets on this brutal POKéMON’s shell are used for high- speed tackles. The rocket cannons on its shell fire jets of water capable of punch­ ing holes through thick steel. It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. Its voracious appetite compels it to devour leaves bigger than itself without hesitation. It releases a terribly strong odor from its antennae. It is covered with a green skin. When it grows, it sheds the skin, covers itself with silk, and becomes a cocoon. If you touch the feeler on top of its head, it will release a horrible stink to protect itself. Its feet have suction cups designed to stick to any surface. It tenaciously climbs trees to forage. It releases a stench from its red antenna to repel enemies. It grows by molting repeatedly. Perhaps because it would like to grow up quickly, it has a voracious appetite, eating a hundred leaves a day. For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antennae on its head to drive away enemies. Caterpie has a voracious appetite. It can devour leaves bigger than its body right before your eyes. From its antenna, this Pokémon releases a terrifically strong odor. When attacked by bird Pokémon, it resists by releasing a terrifically strong odor from its antennae, but it often becomes their prey. For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antenna on its head to drive away enemies. CATERPIE has a voracious appetite. It can devour leaves bigger than its body right before your eyes. From its antenna, this POKéMON releases a terrifically strong odor. It’s easy to catch, and it grows quickly, making it one of the top recommendations for novice Pokémon Trainers. Its body is soft and weak. In nature, its perpetual fate is to be seen by others as food. It crawls into foliage where it camouflages itself among leaves that are the same color as its body. For protection, it releases a horri­ ble stench from the antenna on its head to drive away enemies. Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

It prepares for evolution by hardening its shell as much as possible to protect its soft body. A steel-hard shell protects its tender body. It quietly endures hardships while awaiting evolution. This is its pre- evolved form. At this stage, it can only harden, so it remains motionless to avoid attack. Its shell is filled with a thick liquid. All of the cells throughout its body are being rebuilt in preparation for evolution. This POKéMON is vulnerable to attack while its shell is soft, exposing its weak and tender body. The shell covering this POKéMON’s body is as hard as an iron slab. METAPOD does not move very much. It stays still because it is preparing its soft innards for evolution inside the hard shell.
